        <h2>Is Your Electrical Panel Ready for Modern Life?</h2>
        <p>Your electrical panel is the heart of your home's power system. It distributes electricity to every circuit, and when it cannot keep up with demand, problems follow -- tripped breakers, flickering lights, and potential fire hazards. Many Utah homes built before 2000 still have 100-amp panels or outdated fuse boxes that were never designed for today's electrical loads.</p>
        <p>Osborne Electric upgrades panels to meet current NEC and Utah code requirements, ensuring your home has the capacity to safely power modern appliances, EV chargers, home offices, and more.</p>
        <ul class="value-list">
