        <h2>Signs You Need a Panel Upgrade</h2>
        <p>Electrical panels do not last forever, and an undersized or deteriorating panel poses real safety risks. The following signs indicate your panel may need professional evaluation:</p>
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li>Breakers trip frequently or will not stay reset</li>
          <li>Lights flicker or dim when appliances turn on</li>
          <li>Burning smell or discoloration near the panel</li>
          <li>Panel is warm to the touch</li>
          <li>Home still has a fuse box instead of breakers</li>
          <li>Adding major appliances -- EV charger, hot tub, or workshop</li>
          <li>Planning a home addition or remodel</li>
          <li>Home insurance requires a panel upgrade</li>
        </ul>
